==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Runnel
<hw>Run"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Run</er>.
Cf. <er>Rindle</er>.]</ety> <def>A rivulet or small brook.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bubbling <qex>runnels</qex> joined the sound.</q>
<rj><qau>Collins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By the very sides of the way . . . there are slow
<qex>runnels</qex>, in which one can see the minnows swimming.</q>
<rj><qau>Masson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Runner</ent>⟦br⟧
